Riverside High School is a four-year public high school located in Durham, North Carolina. The current principal is Tonya Williams. (As of 10/31/2016)


== History ==
Opened in 1991 (the first class graduated in 1993), the school currently enrolls approximately 1, 900 students and is one of seven high schools in the Durham Public School System.
